article.headline: Campbell 66, S.C.-Upstate 59
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez scored 23 points to lead Campbell to a 66-59 win over South Carolina-Upstate on Saturday. The Camels (6-9, 2-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) never trailed after Rodriguez's jumper just before the first half buzzer put them ahead 28-27. Campbell then opened the second half on a 25-13 run to take its biggest lead at 53-40 with nine minutes to go. The Spartans (3-14, 1-2) answered with a 12-1 run and trailed just 54-52 with 3:45 left. But they wouldn't get any closer. The Camels hit their final six free throws to seal the win. Campbell made three of its six 3-pointers, while Upstate went 6-of-30 from behind the arc. Bobby Davis had 14 points and eight rebounds to lead the Spartans, while Luke Payne added 12 points. Jake Wohlfeil scored 12 points, while Kyle Vejreska added 10 points for Campbell.
